        "timestamp": "2018-02-08 15:47:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Verified+1\n\nMerging based on the quick fix recommendation from Rich, we need to fix the python verify job. \n\nTracking the details to know what exactly needs to be fixed.\n------\nThe Jenkins job builder project file for optf-osdf specifies a python verify job, but no tox.ini exists in the project repo. The python verify job and tox.ini is not required for the documentation rst files, but might needed be as you add python code to the repo. The doc-verify job also runs (global trigger for any repo with top level docs folder) and succeeds but the failing python verify causes a -1 for patch.\n \nQuick fix:   Manually verify +1, merge your patch\n \nAdd python code and tox.ini -or- update the ci-management/jjb project template to remove the python verify.\n \n----------",
        "patchset_number": 1
